00:37:28,716 --> 00:37:31,011
 What are you trying to say?

407
00:37:31,813 --> 00:37:34,778
Now, draw the fins like this.

408
00:37:36,513 --> 00:37:37,460
That's good.

409
00:37:37,460 --> 00:37:40,926
Hyeon Woo, are you happy now that you've had chocolate milk?

410
00:37:40,926 --> 00:37:43,154
Yes!

411
00:37:43,154 --> 00:37:46,193
You can have a carton a day until Mommy comes home.

412
00:37:46,193 --> 00:37:49,613
- Promise? 
 - Promise.

413
00:37:49,613 --> 00:37:51,427
Hold on.

414
00:37:51,427 --> 00:37:57,201
 I become Gyu Seong's mom and Kang Hyeon's wife, for a perfect life.

415
00:37:57,201 --> 00:37:59,111
 Please help me.

416
00:38:02,120 --> 00:38:04,738
Who is it? That woman from before?

417
00:38:04,738 --> 00:38:06,447
Before?

418
00:38:09,329 --> 00:38:11,522
Do you mean Kim Yi Seol?

419
00:38:12,290 --> 00:38:13,855
Why?

420
00:38:15,867 --> 00:38:17,815
I heard that she will be narrating the exhibition.

421
00:38:17,815 --> 00:38:19,240
Yes.

422
00:38:19,240 --> 00:38:22,508
She seemed really young.

423
00:38:22,508 --> 00:38:24,607
She's different than she looks.

424
00:38:24,607 --> 00:38:27,182
And she's not some young floozy.

425
00:38:27,182 --> 00:38:29,921
She has a strong sense of ethics.

426
00:38:29,921 --> 00:38:32,830
What's that supposed to mean?

427
00:38:34,128 --> 00:38:36,322
Will you look at the time?

428
00:38:36,322 --> 00:38:37,915
It's time to put Hyeon Woo to bed.

429
00:38:37,915 --> 00:38:41,610
Hyeon Woo, say good night to Mommy. It's time to go.

430
00:38:42,897 --> 00:38:44,635
Good night, Mommy.

431
00:38:44,635 --> 00:38:47,761
Good night, Hyeon Woo. I love you.

432
00:38:49,407 --> 00:38:52,317
Call me if you need anything.

433
00:38:52,317 --> 00:38:53,320
Okay.

434
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:54,960
Let's go.

435
00:39:04,291 --> 00:39:06,502
 I'll call you later.

436
00:39:06,502 --> 00:39:09,340
 I'm recuperating after surgery.

437
00:39:20,309 --> 00:39:22,488
Honey!

438
00:39:26,094 --> 00:39:28,209
Honey!

439
00:39:31,020 --> 00:39:32,585
What does

440
00:39:35,230 --> 00:39:39,195
"recuperating" mean?

441
00:39:44,605 --> 00:39:46,170
Who said that?

442
00:39:46,170 --> 00:39:48,710
I was texting Jae Hee,

443
00:39:48,710 --> 00:39:54,112
and she texted, "I'm recuperating after surgery."

444
00:39:54,112 --> 00:39:56,614
I know what surgery is.

445
00:39:56,982 --> 00:40:00,306
But what does "recuperating" mean?

446
00:40:00,306 --> 00:40:06,454
That means that she's recovering her health.

447
00:40:06,454 --> 00:40:09,821
But why did she have surgery?

448
00:40:09,821 --> 00:40:12,198
I don't know.

449
00:40:12,198 --> 00:40:14,329
Hey, where are you going?

450
00:40:14,329 --> 00:40:18,790
I'm sorry, sir. I left something in the office.

451
00:40:54,322 --> 00:40:57,925
Why did you come out? You could have used the call button.

452
00:40:57,925 --> 00:40:59,911
I just wanted to get some fresh air.

453
00:40:59,911 --> 00:41:02,992
Please call me if you need anything.

454
00:41:02,992 --> 00:41:05,170
Of course.

455
00:41:14,704 --> 00:41:17,763
- Hello? 
  - Where are you?

456
00:41:19,015 --> 00:41:20,180
I'm home.

457
00:41:20,180 --> 00:41:24,292
 Is it all right to talk to me from home?

458
00:41:24,292 --> 00:41:28,789
I don't see why not. I've done worse.

459
00:41:29,514 --> 00:41:33,690
Are you all right?

460
00:41:34,619 --> 00:41:37,324
Why wouldn't I be all right?

461
00:41:49,504 --> 00:41:52,130
Were you with Cho Kang Hyeon?

462
00:41:52,130 --> 00:41:54,192
Who was it?

463
00:41:55,809 --> 00:41:58,124
Who did this to you?

464
00:42:00,983 --> 00:42:03,336
 I'm the new CEO of the art center.

465
00:42:03,336 --> 00:42:08,240
And I finally received Hyeon Woo's shares of Sungjin Trade.

466
00:42:11,082 --> 00:42:13,555
Aren't you going to congratulate me?

467
00:42:13,555 --> 00:42:17,736
 Do you think it's just a result of my dirty ambition?

468
00:42:21,283 --> 00:42:24,814
I'm going to continue to contact you.

469
00:42:24,814 --> 00:42:28,550
And I'm going to keep asking for your help.

470
00:42:32,227 --> 00:42:34,855
I won't apologize for yesterday, either.

471
00:42:34,855 --> 00:42:37,600
I've made enough apologies for a lifetime.

472
00:42:38,494 --> 00:42:41,623
 If you don't like it,

473
00:42:41,623 --> 00:42:43,911
you can do what you want.

474
00:44:33,259 --> 00:44:36,881

475
00:44:36,881 --> 00:44:42,830

476
00:45:19,160 --> 00:45:20,793

477
00:45:20,793 --> 00:45:24,990
 It was nice seeing you. See you again.

478
00:46:01,500 --> 00:46:06,633

479
00:46:19,206 --> 00:46:23,939

480
00:46:28,120 --> 00:46:30,397
It was nothing.

481
00:46:31,116 --> 00:46:36,205
It would have passed if you'd just let it.

482
00:46:52,840 --> 00:46:57,480

483
00:47:08,199 --> 00:47:10,326

484
00:47:10,326 --> 00:47:12,622
 Good morning.

485
00:47:29,408 --> 00:47:32,594
 It's nice to hear from you.

486
00:47:34,296 --> 00:47:35,809
Sunbaenim.

487
00:47:35,809 --> 00:47:37,400
Hi.

488
00:47:39,774 --> 00:47:44,082
I heard that tonight will be your final newscast.

489
00:47:44,082 --> 00:47:47,799
I saw the article that you'll be the next Secretary of Civil Affairs.

490
00:47:49,291 --> 00:47:53,604
People will write anything that they want nowadays

491
00:47:53,604 --> 00:47:54,865
without even checking their sources.

492
00:47:54,890 --> 00:47:58,535
And it spreads like wildfire.

493
00:47:59,319 --> 00:48:01,608
People will only see

494
00:48:01,608 --> 00:48:05,607
what they want to see and believe what they want to believe.

495
00:48:05,607 --> 00:48:07,482
Isn't that so?

496
00:48:10,835 --> 00:48:16,450

497
00:48:21,341 --> 00:48:23,743

498
00:48:26,290 --> 00:48:29,060

499
00:48:30,705 --> 00:48:34,480

500
00:48:56,008 --> 00:48:59,986
Mother, how's your schedule today?

501
00:49:01,196 --> 00:49:05,187
We're having the rehearsal for the exhibition narration.

502
00:49:05,187 --> 00:49:08,270
- I can't wait. 
 - Great.

503
00:49:27,196 --> 00:49:30,635
Hello, Jae Hee.

504
00:49:33,311 --> 00:49:34,932
What brings you here?

505
00:49:34,932 --> 00:49:39,330
Didn't you hear that the narrator has been changed?

506
00:49:43,790 --> 00:49:44,968
Are you very busy?

507
00:49:44,968 --> 00:49:48,316
The opening of the exhibition is just around the corner.

508
00:49:48,316 --> 00:49:51,796
It would have been nice if you'd called ahead.

509
00:49:51,796 --> 00:49:54,086
I see.

510
00:49:54,086 --> 00:49:56,889
I was thinking it was like old times, I guess.

511
00:49:58,191 --> 00:50:02,316
We met for the first time seven or eight years ago, right?

512
00:50:02,316 --> 00:50:05,280
It's been so long that I can hardly remember.

513
00:50:05,280 --> 00:50:07,800
I must be getting old.

514
00:50:08,481 --> 00:50:11,816
I wanted to talk to you

515
00:50:11,816 --> 00:50:15,222
the last time I was here.

516
00:50:21,798 --> 00:50:24,813
It was exactly ten years ago.

517
00:50:24,813 --> 00:50:28,229
I was in charge of protocol at the Biennale

518
00:50:28,229 --> 00:50:30,615
while you were at the Ministry of Culture.

519
00:50:30,615 --> 00:50:33,272
That's right.

520
00:50:33,272 --> 00:50:38,613
I guess my memory can't be as good as someone so young.

521
00:50:39,986 --> 00:50:45,208
You were quite old even then.

522
00:50:49,013 --> 00:50:51,595
I was young and foolish,

523
00:50:51,595 --> 00:50:54,997
so I asked you to put me in charge

524
00:50:54,997 --> 00:50:56,483
of the new artist's exhibition.

525
00:50:56,483 --> 00:50:58,402
Oh my!

526
00:50:59,281 --> 00:51:03,198
You certainly had the skills for the job.

527
00:51:03,198 --> 00:51:06,176
Why didn't you get it?

528
00:51:06,806 --> 00:51:08,919
Isn't it obvious?

529
00:51:08,919 --> 00:51:13,009
I couldn't bring myself to go to bed with a dirty old man.

530
00:51:14,113 --> 00:51:16,473
You even gave me your hotel key

531
00:51:16,511 --> 00:51:20,514
to help me get the job.

532
00:51:20,515 --> 00:51:23,217
It was quite unfortunate.

533
00:51:27,894 --> 00:51:31,920
I'm sure you're aware that you are no longer the narrator.

534
00:51:31,920 --> 00:51:36,540
I'll send you an invitation so come back at the opening.

535
00:51:37,311 --> 00:51:39,219
And don't be late.

536
00:52:36,604 --> 00:52:39,484
Hello, my name is Kim Yi Seol.

537
00:52:39,484 --> 00:52:42,894
We will now begin the rehearsal.

538
00:52:45,901 --> 00:52:49,113
A painter but not be obsessed with the object of his art.

539
00:52:49,113 --> 00:52:51,374
However, if he does not struggle with the object,

540
00:52:51,374 --> 00:52:54,037
the painting will lose all tension.

